@@TJvCharMap
<TITLEIMG TJvCustomCharMap>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.GridsAndContent.Grids,JVCL.SelectAndChoose
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Use this component when you want to allow your user to choose a character in a grid displaying the
  current character set.
Description
  TJvCharMap is a grid component similar to the grid available in the CharMap utility included in
  Windows. TJvCharMap can display the characters from any font installed on the system.

  On Unicode enabled operating systems it can also display the Unicode characters as well as the
  Unicode subranges (with some limitations, see TJvCharMapRange.Filter for details).

  TJvCharMap inherits from TJvCustomCharMap and publish many of its properties but does not introduce
  any new behavior.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCharMapRange
Summary
  Provides options for the TJvCharMap component.
Description
  TJvCharMapRange provides display options for a TJvCharMap and is the type for the <LINK
  TJvCustomCharMap.CharRange, CharRange> property.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCharMapRange.EndChar
Summary
  Determines the last character to display in a character map.
Description
  Use EndChar to set the last char to display in a TJvCharMap. Although EndChar is of type Cardinal, it
  is actually used as a WideChar. EndChar has effect only if Filter is set to ufUndefined.
See Also
  TJvCharMapRange.Filter, TJvCharMapRange.StartChar

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCharMapRange.Filter
Summary
  Determines the Unicode subrange to show in a character map.
Description
  Use Filter to set the Unicode subrange for a TJvCharMap. When Filter is ufUndefined, the TJvCharMap
  uses StartChar and EndChar instead.
Note
  Unicode defines several subranges that are non-contiguous. The TJvCharMap can only display contiguous
  character ranges and thus some subranges cannot be displayed in their entirety. The subranges
  affected are ufPrivateUse and ufSpecials.
See Also
  TJvCharMapRange.StartChar, EndChar

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCharMapRange.OnChange
Summary
  Occurs when the current focus changes.
Description
  Write a handler for the OnChange event to take specific action when the user selects another grid
  cell in the control.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCharMapRange.StartChar
Summary
  Determines the first character displayed in a character map.
Description
  Use StartChar to set the first character to display in a TJvCharMap. Although StartChar is of type
  Cardinal, it is actually used as a WideChar. StartChar has effect only if Filter is set to
  ufUndefined.
See Also
  TJvCharMapRange.Filter, EndChar

