@@TJvCustomCharMap
Summary
  Base class for a component that displays characters in a character set in a grid.
Description
  TJvCustomCharMap is the base class for TJvCharMap and defines all its properties and events as
  protected.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomCharMap.AutoSizeHeight
Summary
  Determines whether the component adjusts is height to match its content.
Description
  Set AutoSizeHeight to true to make the control automatically adjust its Height property to display
  its content without using scrollbars.
See Also
  TJvCustomCharMap.AutoSizeWidth

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomCharMap.AutoSizeWidth
Summary
  Determines whether the component adjusts is width to match its content.
Description
  Set AutoSizeWidth to true to make the control automatically adjust its Width property to display its
  content without using scrollbars.
See Also
  TJvCustomCharMap.AutoSizeHeight

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomCharMap.CellSize
Summary
  Returns the current size of a grid cell.
Description
  Call CellSize to learn the current size of a grid cell. The size of a grid cell is automatically
  adjusted to accomodate the size of the currently selected font.
Return value
  A TSize value where cx is the width and cy is the height of a cell.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomCharMap.Character
Summary
  Determines the currently selected character in the grid.
Description
  Read Character to determine the currently selected character in the grid.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomCharMap.CharRange
Summary
  Defines what characters are displayed in the grid.
Description
  Use the properties of CharRange to define what characters are displayed in the grid.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomCharMap.Columns
Summary
  Defines the number of columns to display in the gird.
Description
  Use Columns to read and change the number of columns in the grid. The number of rows is automatically
  adjusted to accomodate the currently selected character range.
See Also
  TJvCustomCharMap.CharRange

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomCharMap.HighlightInvalid
Summary
  Determines whether invalid cells are drawn in another style.
Description
  Use HighlightInvalid to define whether invalid cells are drawn using a background pattern in the
  cell. Invalid characters can be of three types:

  * Characters outside the currently selected range
  * Characters without character info as returned by GetStringTypeEx
  * Characters that have been marked as invalid by an event handler for the OnValidateChar event
See Also
  TJvCustomCharMap.CharRange, TJvCustomCharMap.OnValidateChar

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomCharMap.Locale
Summary
  Determines the locale to use when extracting character info.
Description
  Use Locale to set the locale to use when the character map extracts character info. \Character info
  is extracted using the GetStringTypeEx(W) function and, by default, only characters returning valid
  information is displayed in the grid.
Note
  This property has no function in Unicode enabled operating systems, like Windows 2000 and Windows XP,
  since the Locale parameter is ignored by GetStringTypeExW.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomCharMap.OnSelectChar
Summary
  Event that is called when a character is selected in the grid.
Description
  Write a handler for the OnSelectChar event to take specific actions when the user selects a character
  in the grid. For example, use this event to display information on the currently selected character.
Parameters
  Sender - The component that triggered the event.
  AChar  - The selected character.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomCharMap.OnValidateChar
Summary
  Event that is called when a character needs validating.
Description
  Write a handler for the OnValidateChar event to take specific action when a character needs
  validating. For example, to accept any character, write a handler that always returns true in the
  Valid parameter.
Parameters
  Sender - The component that triggered the event.
  AChar  - The character to validate.
  Valid  - Set to true to mark the character as valid or to false to mark it as invalid.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomCharMap.PanelVisible
Summary
  Shows or hides the zoom panel.
Description
  Use PanelVisible to programmatically show and hide the zoom panel. Note that ShowZoomPanel must be
  true for this setting to have any effect.
See Also
  TJvCustomCharMap.ShowZoomPanel

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomCharMap.ShadowSize
Summary
  Determines the offset of the zoom panel's background shadow.
Description
  Use ShadowSize to set the top/left pixel offset of the shadow behind the zoom panel. Setting this
  value to 0, hides the shadow. The default value is 2 pixels.
See Also
  TJvCustomCharMap.ShowShadow

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomCharMap.ShowShadow
Summary
  Determines whether a shadow is drawn behind the zoom panel.
Description
  Set ShowShadow to true to show a drop shadow behind the zoom panel. On systems that supports it, the
  shadow is alpha blended. On other systems, it is drawn black.
See Also
  TJvCustomCharMap.ShadowSize

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomCharMap.ShowZoomPanel
Summary
  Determines whether clicking a cell in the grid shows a zoom panel or not.
Description
  Use ShowZoomPanel to define whether a zoom panel is shown when the user selects a cell in the grid.

  A zoom panel displays the currently selected character in a larger font and in a separate window
  overlaying the currently selected cell.

  To show the zoom panel at run-time, ShowZoomPanel must be true. The zoom panel can then be displayed
  using any of the following methods:

  * Programmatically by setting PanelVisible to true.
  * By clicking the left mouse button in a valid cell.
  * By selecting a cell and pressing the Enter key.

  Once the zoom panel is visible, the user can use the arrow keys or the mouse scroll wheel to move the
  zoom panel to another cell.
Note
  A user can toggle the zoom panel on and off using the Spacebar and hide it using by pressing the
  Escape key.
See Also
  TJvCustomCharMap.PanelVisible

